article.headline: E. Illinois 58, E. Kentucky 48
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Romain Martin and Billy Parrish each scored 15 points to lead Eastern Illinois to a 58-48 win over Eastern Kentucky on Thursday night. Ousmane Cisse added 12 points and 14 rebounds and Tyler Laser had 10 points for Eastern Illinois (7-9, 4-2 Ohio Valley), which led 26-25 at halftime. The teams traded the lead throughout the second half. A Parrish layup put the Panthers ahead 50-48 with 2:20 left. Eastern Illinois sank eight consecutive free throws to put the game away. Eastern Illinois withstood an onslaught of 3-point attempts by Eastern Kentucky (9-8, 3-4). The Colonels were 11-for-36 from beyond the arc. The Panthers outrebounded the Colonels 44-24. Mike Rose had a game-high 27 points, including seven 3-pointers, for Eastern Kentucky. Josh Taylor fouled out of the game.
